Add 6 GHz band to the World domain and remove NO-IR from US 6 GHz
to enable AP mode on 6 GHz radios.

The World domain (country 00) lacks 6 GHz entries entirely, preventing
devices with world regulatory from using 6 GHz at all. The US domain
has 6 GHz but with NO-IR, which prevents AP mode.

GB and other CEPT countries already work because they include
wmmrule=ETSI on their 6 GHz entries.

This patch:
1. Adds 6 GHz (5925-6425 MHz) to the World domain with NO-OUTDOOR
2. Removes NO-IR from the US 6 GHz entry

Signed-off-by: mingfai <ma@mingf.ai>
---
--- a/db.txt
+++ b/db.txt
@@ -17,6 +17,8 @@ country 00:
 	(5490 - 5730 @ 160), (20), NO-IR, DFS
 	# Channel 149 - 165
 	(5735 - 5835 @ 80), (20), NO-IR
+	# 6 GHz band (5925 - 6425 MHz)
+	(5925 - 6425 @ 320), (12), NO-OUTDOOR, wmmrule=ETSI
 	# IEEE 802.11ad (60GHz), channels 1..3
 	(57240 - 63720 @ 2160), (0)

